---

## Does Caffeine Really Improve Gaming Reflexes?

Caffeine''s a go-to for many gamers, but does it deliver? Studies suggest that 100â€“200 mg (1â€“2 cups of coffee) can boost reaction time by up to 7% for some players. Yet, results vary wildlyâ€”genetics, tolerance, and metabolism play a huge role. One gamer''s edge could be another''s jittery mess.

> **Individual response to caffeine differsâ€”what works for your squad might not work for you.**

Pro tip: Save caffeine for big matches. Daily use builds tolerance, dulling its impact. Want the science? A 2023 study on caffeine and cognition dives deeper.

---

## Why Sleep Is Key to Faster Reaction Time in Gaming

Sleep isn''t optionalâ€”it''s your secret weapon. Research shows 7â€“9 hours of quality rest can improve reaction speed by 3â€“5%. Skimp on sleep (under 6 hours), and you''ll see an 8â€“15% drop in performance. Worse, consecutive bad nights stack the damage, and a single recovery nap won''t fix it.

**Pro Tip**: Stick to a consistent scheduleâ€”like 10 PM to 6 AMâ€”to keep your reflexes razor-sharp. Pair it with a 144Hz monitor, and you''re unstoppable.

